trend_summary: Between first and last scenes, built-up footprint creeps southward from the northern city core, filling gaps along the main highway, while farmland patches shrink and forest regrowth appears in some valleys. Road network densifies and a new interchange and riverside embankment emerge. Overall change is moderate, reflecting steady suburbanisation.
notable_changes: Southward extension of built-up corridor along the primary highway adds several residential enclaves.
Multiple central farmland parcels converted to impervious or construction areas.
New cloverleaf interchange and lane widening visible in the road network.
Gradual increase in contiguous forest cover within western uplands.
